modifiedProp.rawText:
Mrs. Clark is
a social person who gets along with everybody.
The house was recognisable by its green fence and big windows.

Building a house requires
a massive amount of money.

The company's updated logo featured
a blue star in the foreground.
The crowd listened to the famous hymn before the event.

During the financial crisis,
the clever merchant invested in gold.

There are many critics of
the classic prison system today.

Linda used
the short pencil to write a quick note on the fridge.

The little town was known for
its local brewery with long tradition.

For many species,
the quiet forest is an ideal natural habitat.

The little girl liked to sleep with
her lucky toy next to her.

The progress of
the bright student made his teacher very proud.

Mark tried to keep
a normal tone after finding out about the secret.

The hotel guests liked
the warm reception area.
The mountaineers experienced cold feet due to the heavy snowfall.

According to the commission,
the island should be better protected.

Jack visited
the market situated just outside of the city centre.

Mary sold the
old house hidden in the shades of the nearby forest.

For the upcoming performance,
the stage had to be decorated.

The teacher used
a glass to demonstrate the properties of light.
The maintenance of the water pipe made it necessary to close the road.

None of the trainees could work at
the speed set by their supervisor.

The budget included money for
a system upgrade this year.

The professor explained that
the picture dates back to the 1870s.

The company developed a new type of
hair oil intended for everyday use.

The patient reported feeling a strange sensation in
her foot today.

The young family was looking to buy a
new table for their living room.

The military leader examined
the weather map before the operation.

In the library,
the history section was closed due to the ongoing renovations.

The author's book lacked
the quality needed to get a good contract.

Hannah enjoyed
the trendy artworks at the museum of contemporary art.
The building inspector examined the leaky roof of the house.

The bike
was sturdy enough to be used in the mountain.

Jim prepared
a neat outfit for his best friend's wedding.
The children all had a cheery smile on their face at the zoo.
The host family gave a sincere gift to their visitors.
Sarah always tried to make prudent use of her money.

Some citizens were concerned with
the rapid growth of tourism.
People saw Samantha as a nerdy girl who did very well in her studies.

The taxi driver struggled to put
the bulky suitcase in the back of the car.
David's friends were tired of listening to his stale jokes all the time.

Thanks to
the prompt response of the mayor, the dispute was resolved.

Many spectators were fascinated by
the wavy hair of the lead actress.
Alex is the avid type of golfer who plays every weekend.
In the big city, there was a dire need for more family houses.

Last night, Joseph stopped by
the pawn shop on his way home.
During the summer, the motel attracted many tourists with its low prices.

The documentary showed a series
of heist cases that remain unsolved.

Not long after
the brawl escalated in the bar, the police was called.
The large production of maize was a big boost for the economy.

The manager asked
the clerk to be careful with the paperwork.
The lack of haze in the park made it possible to conduct the field experiment.
The discovery of the missing folder shed new light on the police investigation.
The new theory led to a paradox which was seemingly very difficult to solve.

Vanessa realised she had forgotten
her purse when she was in the shop.

The dog barked at
the crow nesting in the branches of the tree.
Margaret benefited a lot from the advice of her mentor during her school years.
Sally bought flowers for the doorway upon moving into her new house.

After finishing
his lecture early, the student was free to go home.

After the house was fully cleaned,
the porch shined in the sunlight.

text.rawText: You will read short sentences and answer questions about them. Read the sentences silently in your head for comprehension.

Before a sentence appears, you will see a fixation cross on the left. You will see an example of it on the next page. Look at the fixation cross until it disappears. If the fixation cross does not disappear within 10s, click the right arrow key to skip it.
+
Mary bought some apples on the way home.
You will be asked to read a sentence such as this one. Don't forget to click the mouse when you finish reading.
You will then be asked to answer a question about the sentence. Click with the mouse to select yes or no.
Did Mary buy milk?
We will now do a few practice trials to get used to the task.
+
While he fixed the mower, his 17 year old son was milking the cows.
Click the mouse to continue.
Was the son fixing the tractor?
+
The experienced caricaturist drew the child with the big ears.
Click the mouse to continue
Did the child have big ears?
+
They took a trip to the Amazon rainforest and saw many amazing creatures.
Click the mouse to continue
Did they travel to the Sahara desert?
+
While Tom grilled the sausages, his wife entertained the guests.
Click the mouse to continue.
Did Tom's wife grill sausages?
+
As Henry whittled the stick for roasting marshmallows, his father put another log in the fire.
Click the mouse to continue.
Were they roasting marhmellos?
This is the end of the practice. You will now start with the real experiment.

entities.name: Subject_Nr
entities.description: The variable "Subject_Nr" is a global counter of participants in a study. This can be used to do custom between subject randomization and to infer the overall number of participants in a study.

entities.name: Trial_Nr
entities.description: The variable "Trial_Nr" holds the current value of the "trial nr" for the current task. This can be used to infer whether the participant currently performs the first, second, third,(and so on) trial in this task.

entities.name: Trial_Id
entities.description: The variable "Trial_Id" holds the current value of the "trial id" for the current task. This can be used to infer which Trial is currently performed by the participant.

entities.name: Condition_Id
entities.description: The variable "Condition_Id" holds the current value of the "condition id" for the current trial. This can be used to infer which condition is currently performed by the participant.

entities.name: Subject_Code
entities.description: The variable "Subject_Code" is a unique string for each subject / session across all experiments running on Labvanced. This can be used to uniquely identify each participant or session.

entities.name: Group_Name
entities.description: The variable "Group_Name" holds the value of the "subject group name" for each participant. This can be used to infer to which subject group each participant is assigned to.

entities.name: Start_Time_Local
entities.description: The variable "Start_Time_Local" records the start time of the current participant session in UNIX time.

entities.name: End_Time_Local
entities.description: The variable "End_Time_Local" records the end time of the current participant session in UNIX time.

entities.name: Session_Name
entities.description: The variable "Session_Name" holds the value of the "session name" for the current session. This can be used to infer which session is currently performed by the participant.

entities.name: Session_Nr
entities.description: The variable "Session_Nr" holds the current value of the "session nr" for the current session. This can be used to infer whether the participant currently performs the first, second, third,(and so on) session.

entities.name: Block_Name
entities.description: The variable "Block_Name" holds the current value of the "block name" for the current session. This can be used to infer which block is currently performed by the participant.

entities.name: Block_Nr
entities.description: The variable "Bock_Nr" holds the current value of the "block nr" for the current session. This can be used to infer whether the participant currently performs the first, second, third,(and so on) block in this session.

entities.name: Task_Name
entities.description: The variable "Task_Name" holds the current value of the "task name" for the current block. This can be used to infer which task is currently performed by the participant.

entities.name: Task_Nr
entities.description: The variable "Task_Nr" holds the current value of the "task nr" for the current block. This can be used to infer whether the participant currently performs the first, second, third,(and so on) task in this block.

entities.name: TimeMeasure_Mean
entities.description: The variable "TimeMeasure_Mean" provides an estimate of the mean value of how precise callback functions work on the participants device. Hence this is a measure of how precise stimuli are be presented temporally, but not a measure of reaction time reliability (which is usually better).

entities.name: TimeMeasure_Std
entities.description: The variable "TimeMeasure_Std" provides an estimate of the standard deviation of how precise callback functions work on the participants device. Hence this is a measure of how variable stimuli presentation is temporally.

entities.name: Crowdsourcing_Code
entities.description: The variable "Crowdsourcing_Code" holds the value of the unique "crowdsourcing code", typically shown to the subject at end of the experiment to complete the crowdsourcing session and claim the payment.

entities.name: Crowdsourcing_SubjId
entities.description: The variable "Crowdsourcing_SubjId" holds the value of the unique "identification code" for each crowdsourcing participant. This can be used to later on create a reference between crowdsourcing data on Labvanced and the external crowdsourcing service (e.g Prolific or Mechanical Turk).

entities.name: Screen_Refresh_Rate
entities.description: This variable "Screen_Refresh_Rate" provides the information of participant device Screen Refresh Rate in "Hz" unit

entities.name: Subject_Nr_Per_Group
entities.description: The variable "Subject_Nr_Per_Group" is a counter per subject group in a study. This can be used to do custom between subject randomization and to infer the current number of participants within each subject group.

entities.name: Role_Id
entities.description: The variable "Role_ID" is used for multi user/multi participant studies to refer uniquely to one of the participants of the study. This can be used to present different frames and roles to different participants within the same task/experiment.

entities.name: Multi_User_Group_Id
entities.description: This variable holds a unique group ID for multi user studies.

entities.name: Displayed_Language
entities.description: The variable "Displayed Language" holds the value of the selected display language, only if there were 2 or more languages to select from. This value can be used to show different content, i.e. texts for different language settings.

entities.name: Window_Width_In_Pixels
entities.description: This variable holds the number of pixels in the X-dimension of the experiment window in pixels.

entities.name: Window_Height_In_Pixels
entities.description: This variable holds the number of pixels in the Y-dimension of the experiment window in pixels.

entities.name: Screen_Width_In_Pixels
entities.description: This variable holds the number of pixels in the X-dimension of the computer screen in pixels.

entities.name: Screen_Height_In_Pixels
entities.description: This variable holds the number of pixels in the Y-dimension of the computer screen in pixels.

entities.name: Pixel_Density_PerMM
entities.description: This variable hold the number of pixels per millimeter of the screen.

entities.name: Experiment_Version
entities.description: This variable holds the version of the experiment that is autoincremented when the study is saved.

entities.name: Distance_To_Screen_In_CM
entities.description: This variable holds the value of the selected /adjusted distance to screen of a subject

entities.name: FaceDetectionRate
entities.description: This variable holds the value of how fast the face detection worked in detections per second.

entities.name: Browser_Spec
entities.description: The variable "Browser_Spec" holds the value of the browser used by the participant to perform the experiment. This can be used to later analyze possible differences between browsers. Allowing/forbidding certain browsers can be done via the study settings.

entities.name: System_Spec
entities.description: The variable "System_Spec" holds the value of the operating system/device used by the participant to perform the experiment. This can be used to later analyze possible differences between operating systems/devices. Allowing/forbidding certain operating systems/devices can be done via the study settings.

entities.name: Agent_Spec
entities.description: The variable "Agent_Spec" holds the complete String of the "User-Agent-Browser-Specification". This can be used to get some more detailed information about the participants system specifications.

entities.name: BrowserVersion_Spec
entities.description: The variable "BrowserVersion_Spec" holds the value of the browser version used by the participant to perform the experiment. This can be used to later analyze possible differences between browser versions.

entities.name: Is_Fullscreen
entities.description: The variable "Is_Fullscreen" is a boolean value, which indicates whether the experiment viewport is currently shown in fullscreen mode.

entities.name: Always_Fullscreen
entities.description: The variable "Always_Fullscreen", is a boolean value, which is true as long as the participant keeps the experiment running in fullscreen mode. This can be used to pause/quit the experiment when a participant leaves the fullscreen mode.

entities.name: SelectedGender
entities.description: This variable holds the value of the selected gender in the initial (pre-study) questionnaire.

entities.name: SelectedAge
entities.description: This variable holds the value of the selected age in the initial (pre-study) questionnaire.

entities.name: SelectedLocation
entities.description: This variable holds the value of the selected location in the initial (pre-study) questionnaire.

entities.name: SelectedLanguage
entities.description: This variable holds the value of the selected (first) language in the initial (pre-study) questionnaire.

entities.name: Group_Nr
entities.description: The variable "Group_Nr" holds the value of the "subject group nr" for each participant. This can be used to infer to which subject group each participant is assigned to.

entities.name: Start_Time
entities.description: The variable "Start_Time" records the start time of the current participant session in UTC time.

entities.name: End_Time
entities.description: The variable "End_Time" records the end time of the current participant session in UTC time.

entities.name: Exp_Subject_Id
entities.description: The variable "Exp_Subject_Id" holds the current value of the "subject_id" for the current session.

entities.name: Completed
entities.description: The variable "Completed" holds the information either recording was successfully completed or not.

entities.name: Rec_Session_Id
entities.description: The variable "Rec_Session_Id" holds the unique value of the current session.

entities.name: Session_Token
entities.description: The variable "Session_Token" holds the token information to start the next session of a longitudinal study.

Approximately how far away are you sitting from the monitor in centimeters?
